+`T-214-01`:
+Patched the fallback preview payload so it now keeps `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when `preview_enabled=false`. The router now normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building either preview shape.
+
+`T-214-02`:
+Classified as duplicate of `T-214-01`. No separate code change was needed because the same fallback regression is fixed by the preview and router updates above.
+
+`T-214-03`:
+Classified as obsolete. The comment points at an outdated diff hunk, and I did not revive any legacy preview branch on the current branch.
+
+`T-214-04`:
+Added regression coverage in `tests/test_preview.py` for `preview_enabled=false` with `approval_state=\"manual_review\"`, asserting normalization to `human_review_required` and `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+`T-214-05`:
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example now includes `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`.
